"v.退潮；衰退 【英】 v. 退潮(to flow back; recede)；衰退(decline; wane) 【例】 Water washed up on the shore , then slowly ebbed away. The politician's popularity has ebbed. v. 退潮 = recede; 衰退 = decline = wane 【记】读: 爱波. 虽然爱的波浪在我们这一代有越演越烈之趋势, 但那是时间上的提前, 而非强度的增高; 尤其是对于考G一族, 更是需要降降温, 退退潮, 专心于本职工作. 【记】近于abate；音：哀悲，哀兵，悲哀的士兵士气衰落→衰退；音: 矮波，矮小的波浪→退潮；音：矮泊，停泊在海中的船矮下去，因为退潮了 ebb (n.)  Old English ebba ""ebb, low tide,"" perhaps from Proto-Germanic *abjon (cognates: Old Frisian ebba, Old Saxon ebbiunga, Middle Dutch ebbe, Dutch eb, German Ebbe), from *ab-, from PIE root *apo- ""off, away"" (see apo-). Figurative sense of ""decline, decay"" is c.1400. ebb (v.)  Old English ebbian, from the root of ebb (n.). Related: Ebbed; ebbing."
